
====================================================================
HashiCorp Vault — Akamai Marketplace
====================================================================

Vault UI:  https://{{ _domain }}/
Vault API: https://{{ _domain }}/v1/

Initial unseal keys and the root token are in:
    /home/{{ username }}/.credentials   (mode 0600)

FIRST RUN
  1. Review the credentials file:    cat ~/.credentials
  2. Open the UI and sign in with the Initial Root Token.
  3. Distribute the 5 unseal keys to 5 separate operators.
  4. Rotate the root token (instructions in the credentials file).
  5. Shred the credentials file once keys are distributed.

OPERATIONAL NOTES
  - If Vault becomes sealed after a reboot, unseal it with 3 of 5 keys:
        VAULT_ADDR=https://{{ _domain }} vault operator unseal <key>
  - Audit log:        /var/log/vault/audit.log
  - Logrotate config: /etc/logrotate.d/vault  (weekly, keep 12, copytruncate)
  - Cert renewal:     handled by certbot's system timer (--nginx plugin)
                      systemctl list-timers | grep certbot

====================================================================
